      Meme activism
   =20
 =20
The basic issue is that right now everything is dumb. You can complain abou=
t that, or you can embrace it. In investing in 2021, =E2=80=9Cmy channel ch=
ecks and fundamental modeling suggest that this company will grow earnings =
faster than the market expects so I will buy it with a price target 20% abo=
ve today=E2=80=99s price=E2=80=9D might=C2=A0sound=C2=A0smarter than =E2=80=
=9Cthis company=E2=80=99s chief executive officer just tweeted a picture of=
 a dog at Elon Musk so I=E2=80=99m going to buy out-of-the-money call optio=
ns expiring Friday because the stock will go up 200% today,=E2=80=9D but th=
e latter approach happens to work better right now.=C2=A0This is all well a=
nd good if you=E2=80=99re a retail investor on Reddit; you just buy the rig=
ht memes at the right time and get rich. (This is=C2=A0really, really=C2=A0=
not investing advice!) You are essentially a passive observer; your job is =
to notice which companies are doing the dumbest things and then buy them. (=
Read the previous parenthetical!)But other people are active participants i=
n this dumb economy and can nudge companies to be dumber so their stocks wi=
ll go up. This most obviously works for the chief executive officers of com=
panies. If you are the CEO of a public company, I want you to consider very=
 seriously going to an investment conference with no pants on. Your stock w=
ill go up, your shareholders will be happy and your cost of financing will =
go down. =E2=80=9CWhy would my stock go up because I don=E2=80=99t wear pan=
ts,=E2=80=9D you ask me, and I say, shh, shh, it just will, don=E2=80=99t a=
sk why. =E2=80=9CI have my dignity, I am not going to go to an important bu=
siness conference with no pants on just to amuse some apes on Reddit,=E2=80=
=9D you say, and I say: You are not as committed to maximizing shareholder =
value as I thought you were.=C2=A0I  wrote last month:There is a traditiona=
l view of corporate social media in which a board would tell its chief exec=
utive officer to be cautious and anodyne on Twitter. There are many things =
that can go wrong with an unhinged Twitter presence, and not a lot that can=
 go right, is what your lawyer would probably tell you. But the last few ye=
ars have altered that calculation, and now the things that can go right are=
 like =E2=80=9Craising billions of dollars of retail capital when you need =
it most,=C2=A0at all-time-high valuations.=E2=80=9D Arguably=C2=A0it=E2=80=
=99s a breach of fiduciary duties=C2=A0not=C2=A0to be weird on Twitter all =
the time.But a similar analysis works for professional activist investors. =
If you are an activist and you are writing a letter to the CEO of an underp=
erforming company saying =E2=80=9Cyou should sell off your non-core divisio=
ns and return the cash to shareholders,=E2=80=9D I want you to tear up that=
 letter and instead write one saying =E2=80=9Cyou should order Teslas for a=
ll of your employees, put a picture of a Shiba Inu on all of your products,=
=C2=A0and announce that your non-core divisions will now mine crypto.=E2=80=
=9D Is this a good use of shareholder money? Man, who cares, the point is t=
hat the stock will go up 200% and you=E2=80=99ll be able to sell your posit=
ion at a huge profit. I once=C2=A0wrote some advice for activists:Buy some =
stock in a struggling company and, instead of going out and pitching your p=
lans to BlackRock and Vanguard, get on Reddit and say like =E2=80=9Cif my b=
oard slate is elected we=E2=80=99re gonna take XYZ Co. to the moon and sque=
eze those short sellers, rocket emoji rocket emoji rocket emoji, not a prox=
y solicitation, read my SEC filings for full disclosures.=E2=80=9D Draw a p=
icture of an ape riding a rocket and slap it on your proxy statement. Call =
your activist fund Diamond Hands Capital LP.=C2=A0Basically you want to buy=
 stock in a company, push it to become a meme stock, and then sell the stoc=
k at a huge profit to people on Reddit.Here is, I guess, a real letter from=
 real activist investor NuOrion Advisors[1] to the chairman and CEO of Macy=
=E2=80=99s Inc.:Macy=E2=80=99s share price is materially undervalued and re=
quires urgent action to unlock value. We believe that by adopting the strat=
egies discussed below, Macy=E2=80=99s would be worth more than $75 per shar=
e.Macy=E2=80=99s should form partnerships with EV car companies (e.g. Tesla=
, Lucid or Rivian) to showcase their products on the ground floor of Macy=
=E2=80=99s 100 top landmark stores (e.g. Herald Square, Marshall Field, Uni=
on Square) and to use their massive parking footprint to build an EV chargi=
ng network. Atom Power, a leader in EV charging, is adding more than a 1000=
 charge points in NYC alone- Atom Power could similarly add charging statio=
ns throughout the Macy=E2=80=99s store footprint. We believe that direct as=
sociation with EV companies will drive enormous traffic to Macy=E2=80=99s s=
tores.In addition, Macy=E2=80=99s should announce immediately that they are=
 partnering with various Crypto platforms to allow digital payments. Macy=
=E2=80=99s can be one of the first major retailers to accept Crypto, joinin=
g companies like Starbucks and Whole Foods.There=E2=80=99s more but those a=
re the main things. =E2=80=9CMacy=E2=80=99s should put out a press release =
about electric cars and another one about crypto,=E2=80=9D is the gist here=
. Honestly that is the best corporate finance advice you=E2=80=99re gonna g=
et in November 2021! It=E2=80=99s stupid, sure =E2=80=94=C2=A0people are go=
ing to drive into the=C2=A0Macy=E2=80=99s in Herald Square=C2=A0to charge t=
heir Teslas??????=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0and it is not, like, sophisticated di=
fferentiated advice; anyone on Reddit could have told you to do this. But i=
t is=C2=A0correct.Of course public companies resist doing these obvious tra=
des because, you know, they make absolutely no business sense.=C2=A0What I =
am saying here is, let go of that. Say words about crypto. Say words about =
electric cars. Tweet a picture of a dog. Your stock will go up. Your shareh=
olders will be rich and happy. You can raise lots of money to finance norma=
l good businessy things, because your stock is at an all-time high, because=
 you got in a fight with Elon Musk on Twitter or changed your avatar to a B=
ored Ape or whatever. Lower your cost of capital. Embrace the stupidity.Her=
e is NuOrion=E2=80=99s actual case for crashing lots of Teslas through the =
windows of Macy=E2=80=99s stores:Macys.com needs to have competitive access=
 to capital, the ability to attract additional top talent, and the agility =
of modern online fashion to best serve its customers.This is the GameStop s=
trategy.[2] GameStop Corp. became the great meme stock of 2021, partly thro=
ugh some promising business developments but mostly through somewhat out-of=
-the-blue Reddit enthusiasm. But because it was a meme, it had huge busines=
s advantages in terms of =E2=80=9Ccompetitive access to capital=E2=80=9D an=
d =E2=80=9Cability to attract additional top talent.=E2=80=9D I  wrote in J=
une:A year ago, GameStop=E2=80=99s stock closed at $5.07 per share, down 7%=
 year-over-year, and it was not hiring talent from Amazon or raising a bill=
ion dollars by selling stock. Yesterday, GameStop=E2=80=99s stock closed at=
 $302.56, up 5,867% year-over-year, and it is. =E2=80=A6 This is as close a=
s you=E2=80=99re ever going to come to a company=E2=80=99s stock going up 5=
,000% in a few months for no reason. Seems like that might be good for busi=
ness!=C2=A0If you can make your stock go up for dumb reasons, you can sell =
stock for a lot of money and use the money to do good things that make your=
 stock go up for good reasons. Though honestly that is not too relevant to =
the activist investor, who can just sell when the stock goes up for the dum=
b reasons. =E2=80=9CDo crypto and electric-vehicle memes=E2=80=9D is to 202=
1 activism what =E2=80=9Cdo stock buybacks=E2=80=9D was to 2016 activism. T=
hey=E2=80=99re a little short-termist! But they=E2=80=99re what the market =
wants.I suppose the value added by the activist here is, like =E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0credibility? Again, I think that if you are the CEO of a public company =
you should absolutely go around getting in Twitter fights and not wearing p=
ants and talking about crypto. But if you go to your board of directors wit=
h this strategy they will say =E2=80=9Cwhat?=E2=80=9D and you will say =E2=
=80=9Cthis is what shareholders like these days=E2=80=9D and they will say =
=E2=80=9Cwhat?=E2=80=9D and you will say =E2=80=9Clook at these comments I =
found on Reddit=E2=80=9D and they will say =E2=80=9Cwhat?=E2=80=9D and it w=
ill not necessarily be the productive conversation you want. Whereas if an =
activist sends a company a letter saying =E2=80=9Cdo the crypto thing=E2=80=
=9D then that is tangible evidence that your shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0yo=
ur real, professional, institutional shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0want you t=
o start memeing it up. What are you waiting for?
