 subscribe to Money Stuff and other great Bloomberg newsletters here. Thank=
s![1] =E2=80=9CNuOrion Advisors is a private investment firm that makes dir=
ect investments in undervalued corporate fallen angels that can regain thei=
r economic strength,=E2=80=9D says its press release. The Wall Street Journ=
al described=C2=A0it in connection with an activist situation at Avon Produ=
cts Inc. in 2015: =E2=80=9CNuOrion was formed in 2014 to invest in troubled=
 companies. Its investments are funded by wealthy families on a deal-by-dea=
l basis. It was founded by Guy Phillips, former head of the global consumer=
 and retail investment-banking business at UBS Group AG, who first approach=
ed Barington with the idea of investing in Avon.=E2=80=9D[2] Except that Ga=
meStop did not really choose to become a meme stock; that just sort of happ=
ened exogenously. Arguably this is the *Tesla* strategy: Do memes, get a re=
tail following, sell stock, etc. But it is also the AMC strategy. It=E2=80=
=99s  the Microstrategy strategy. CEOs understand now that doing meme-y thi=
ngs can lower their cost of capital.=C2=A0[3] Arguably another inaccuracy i=
s that I say that Credit Suisse loaned Archegos money to buy stocks, wherea=
s in fact Archegos mostly=C2=A0bought those stocks synthetically through to=
tal return swaps with Credit Suisse, but again those are functionally the s=
ame thing.[4] One reason Hwang came in through that door is that he *used t=
o* manage a big hedge fund =E2=80=94=C2=A0Tiger Asia =E2=80=94=C2=A0and so =
was sort of accustomed to that service. If you run a hedge fund and then re=
turn all your=C2=A0outside money to manage your own wealth, that=E2=80=99s =
a =E2=80=9Cfamily office,=E2=80=9D but everyone still treats it like a hedg=
e fund.
