om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Meme activism</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic issue is that right now ever=
ything is dumb. You can complain about that, or you can embrace it. In inve=
sting in 2021, =E2=80=9Cmy channel checks and fundamental modeling suggest =
that this company will grow earnings faster than the market expects so I wi=
ll buy it with a price target 20% above today=E2=80=99s price=E2=80=9D migh=
t=C2=A0<em>sound=C2=A0</em>smarter than =E2=80=9Cthis company=E2=80=99s chi=
ef executive officer just tweeted a picture of a dog at Elon Musk so I=E2=
=80=99m going to buy out-of-the-money call options expiring Friday because =
the stock will go up 200% today,=E2=80=9D but the latter approach happens t=
o work better right now.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is all =
well and good if you=E2=80=99re a retail investor on Reddit; you just buy t=
he right memes at the right time and get rich. (This is=C2=A0<em>really, re=
ally=C2=A0</em>not investing advice!) You are essentially a passive observe=
r; your job is to notice which companies are doing the dumbest things and t=
hen buy them. (Read the previous parenthetical!)</p><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">But other people are active participants in this dumb economy and can=
 nudge companies to be dumber so their stocks will go up. This most obvious=
ly works for the chief executive officers of companies. If you are the CEO =
of a public company, I want you to consider very seriously going to an inve=
stment conference <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
25582014.262653/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaW5kZXBlbmRlbnQuY28udWsvbmV3cy93b3JsZC9hbWV=
yaWNhcy9hbWMtY2VvLXBhbnRzLXlvdXR1YmUtaW50ZXJ2aWV3LWIxODYxMjI3Lmh0bWw/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB9e8dc4ca" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">with no pants on</a>. Your stock will =
go up, your shareholders will be happy and your cost of financing will go d=
own. =E2=80=9CWhy would my stock go up because I don=E2=80=99t wear pants,=
=E2=80=9D you ask me, and I say, shh, shh, it just will, don=E2=80=99t ask =
why. =E2=80=9CI have my dignity, I am not going to go to an important busin=
ess conference with no pants on just to amuse some apes on Reddit,=E2=80=9D=
 you say, and I say: You are not as <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/25582014.262653/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9tYXR0X2xldmluZ=
S9zdGF0dXMvMTQ1NTg5NjMxNDIxOTIyNTA5MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbfc8dbe4" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;">committed to maximizing shareholder value</a> as I thought you were.=
=C2=A0I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25582014.2=
62653/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtM=
TkvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1nYW1lc3RvcC1iYWZmbGVzLXRoZS1zZWMtdG9v=
P2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMDQyMV9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1=
uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIxMTEwNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB198d96f6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> wrote last month</a>:</p><blockquote><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a traditional view of corporate social=
 media in which a board would tell its chief executive officer to be cautio=
us and anodyne on Twitter. There are many things that can go wrong with an =
unhinged Twitter presence, and not a lot that can go right, is what your la=
wyer would probably tell you. But the last few years have altered that calc=
ulation, and now the things that can go right are like =E2=80=9Craising bil=
lions of dollars of retail capital when you need it most,=C2=A0at all-time-=
high valuations.=E2=80=9D Arguably=C2=A0it=E2=80=99s a breach of fiduciary =
duties=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>to be weird on Twitter all the time.</p></blo=
ckquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But a similar analysis works for profe=
ssional activist investors. If you are an activist and you are writing a le=
tter to the CEO of an underperforming company saying =E2=80=9Cyou should se=
ll off your non-core divisions and return the cash to shareholders,=E2=80=
=9D I want you to tear up that letter and instead write one saying =E2=80=
=9Cyou should order Teslas for all of your employees, put a picture of a Sh=
iba Inu on all of your products,=C2=A0and announce that your non-core divis=
ions will now mine crypto.=E2=80=9D Is this a good use of shareholder money=
? Man, who cares, the point is that the stock will go up 200% and you=E2=80=
=99ll be able to sell your position at a huge profit. I once=C2=A0<a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25582014.262653/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDgtMTIvY3JlZGl0LXN1=
aXNzZS1zLW9vcHNpZS1ib25kcy1nby1kb3duP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMDQyMV9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV=
0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIxMTEwNCZ1dG=
1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB39669715" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">wro=
te some advice for activists</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">Buy some stock in a struggling company and, instead of going out and pit=
ching your plans to BlackRock and Vanguard, get on Reddit and say like =E2=
=80=9Cif my board slate is elected we=E2=80=99re gonna take XYZ Co. to the =
moon and squeeze those short sellers, rocket emoji rocket emoji rocket emoj=
i, not a proxy solicitation, read my SEC filings for full disclosures.=E2=
=80=9D Draw a picture of an ape riding a rocket and slap it on your proxy s=
tatement. Call your activist fund Diamond Hands Capital LP.=C2=A0</p></bloc=
kquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Basically you want to buy stock in a co=
mpany, push it to become a meme stock, and then sell the stock at a huge pr=
ofit to people on Reddit.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is, I guess,=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25582014.262653/a=
HR0cHM6Ly9udW9yaW9uYWR2aXNvcnNidXNpbmVzcy5maWxlcy53b3JkcHJlc3MuY29tLzIwMjEv=
MTEvbGV0dGVyLXRvLW0tY2hhaXJtYW4tMy5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfdf0c73a" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">a real letter</a> from real activist investor NuOrion Advisors[1] t=
o the chairman and CEO of Macy=E2=80=99s Inc.:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">Macy=E2=80=99s share price is materially undervalued and re=
quires urgent action to unlock value. We believe that by adopting the strat=
egies discussed below, Macy=E2=80=99s would be worth more than $75 per shar=
e.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Macy=E2=80=99s should form partnerships =
with EV car companies (e.g. Tesla, Lucid or Rivian) to showcase their produ=
cts on the ground floor of Macy=E2=80=99s 100 top landmark stores (e.g. Her=
ald Square, Marshall Field, Union Square) and to use their massive parking =
footprint to build an EV charging network. Atom Power, a leader in EV charg=
ing, is adding more than a 1000 charge points in NYC alone- Atom Power coul=
d similarly add charging stations throughout the Macy=E2=80=99s store footp=
rint. We believe that direct association with EV companies will drive enorm=
ous traffic to Macy=E2=80=99s stores.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In ad=
dition, Macy=E2=80=99s should announce immediately that they are partnering=
 with various Crypto platforms to allow digital payments. Macy=E2=80=99s ca=
n be one of the first major retailers to accept Crypto, joining companies l=
ike Starbucks and Whole Foods.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>There=E2=80=99s more but those are the main things. =E2=80=9CMacy=E2=80=99=
s should put out a press release about electric cars and another one about =
crypto,=E2=80=9D is the gist here. Honestly that is the best corporate fina=
nce advice you=E2=80=99re gonna get in November 2021! It=E2=80=99s stupid, =
sure =E2=80=94=C2=A0<em>people are going to drive into the=C2=A0Macy=E2=80=
=99s in Herald Square=C2=A0to charge their Teslas??????=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=94=
=C2=A0and it is not, like, sophisticated differentiated advice; anyone on R=
eddit could have told you to do this. But it is=C2=A0<em>correct</em>.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course public companies resist doing these o=
bvious trades because, you know, they make absolutely no business sense.=C2=
=A0What I am saying here is, let go of that. Say words about crypto. Say wo=
rds about electric cars. Tweet a picture of a dog. Your stock will go up. Y=
our shareholders will be rich and happy. You can raise lots of money to fin=
ance normal good businessy things, because your stock is at an all-time hig=
h, because you got in a fight with Elon Musk on Twitter or changed your ava=
tar to a Bored Ape or whatever. Lower your cost of capital. Embrace the stu=
pidity.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is NuOrion=E2=80=99s actual ca=
se for crashing lots of Teslas through the windows of Macy=E2=80=99s stores=
:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Macys.com needs to have compe=
titive access to capital, the ability to attract additional top talent, and=
 the agility of modern online fashion to best serve its customers.</p></blo=
ckquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is the GameStop strategy.[2] Game=
Stop Corp. became the great meme stock of 2021, partly through some promisi=
ng business developments but mostly through somewhat out-of-the-blue Reddit=
 enthusiasm. But because it was a meme, it had huge business advantages in =
terms of =E2=80=9Ccompetitive access to capital=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cabili=
ty to attract additional top talent.=E2=80=9D I <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25582014.262653/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnL=
mNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDYtMTAvbWF5YmUtZ2FtZXN0b3AtaXMtZ29vZC1u=
b3c_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEwNDIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmN=
lPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMTA0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB1ea32890" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> wrote in June</a>:</p><blockquote><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A year ago, GameStop=E2=80=99s stock closed at $=
5.07 per share, down 7% year-over-year, and it was not hiring talent from A=
mazon or raising a billion dollars by selling stock. Yesterday, GameStop=E2=
=80=99s stock closed at $302.56, up 5,867% year-over-year, and it is. =E2=
=80=A6 This is as close as you=E2=80=99re ever going to come to a company=
=E2=80=99s stock going up 5,000% in a few months for no reason. Seems like =
that might be good for business!=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">If you can make your stock go up for dumb reasons, you can sell st=
ock for a lot of money and use the money to do good things that make your s=
tock go up for good reasons. Though honestly that is not too relevant to th=
e activist investor, who can just sell when the stock goes up for the dumb =
reasons. =E2=80=9CDo crypto and electric-vehicle memes=E2=80=9D is to 2021 =
activism what =E2=80=9Cdo stock buybacks=E2=80=9D was to 2016 activism. The=
y=E2=80=99re a little short-termist! But they=E2=80=99re what the market wa=
nts.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suppose the value added by the activ=
ist here is, like =E2=80=A6=C2=A0credibility? Again, I think that if you ar=
e the CEO of a public company you should absolutely go around getting in Tw=
itter fights and not wearing pants and talking about crypto. But if you go =
to your board of directors with this strategy they will say =E2=80=9Cwhat?=
=E2=80=9D and you will say =E2=80=9Cthis is what shareholders like these da=
ys=E2=80=9D and they will say =E2=80=9Cwhat?=E2=80=9D and you will say =E2=
=80=9Clook at these comments I found on Reddit=E2=80=9D and they will say =
=E2=80=9C<em>what?</em>=E2=80=9D and it will not necessarily be the product=
ive conversation you want. Whereas if an activist sends a company a letter =
saying =E2=80=9Cdo the crypto thing=E2=80=9D then that is tangible evidence=
 that your shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0your real, professional, institution=
al shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0want you to start memeing it up. What are yo=
u waiting for?</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D"au=
to" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0">
